  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
      <div xml:id="NA202-kiḷavi">
        <p type="edition">itu uṭaṉpōkāniṉṟa talaimakaṉ talaimakaṭkuc colliyatu.</p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">This is what HE who was eloping [with her] said to HER.</p>
      </div>
      <div xml:id="NA202">
        <lg type="edition">
<l>            puliporac civanta pulālañ ceṅkōṭ</l>
<l>            ṭolipaṉ mutta mārppa valiciṟantu</l>
<l>            vaṉcuvaṟ parārai murukkik kaṉṟoṭu</l>
<l>            maṭappiṭi taḻīiya taṭakkai vēḻan</l>
<l>            tēṉcey peruṅkiḷai yirīiya vēṅkaip </l>
<l>            poṉpurai kavaḻam puṟantaru pūṭṭu</l>
<l>            māmalai viṭarakaṅ kavaiik kāṇvarak</l>
<l>            kaṇṭiciṉ vāḻiyō kuṟumaka ṇuntai</l>
<l>            yaṟumīṉ payanta vaṟañcey tiṅkaṭ</l>
<l>            celcuṭar neṭuṅkoṭi pōlap </l>
<l>            palpūṅ kōṅka maṇinta kāṭē.</l>
        </lg>
        <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>While [we?] are coming to see jointly(?) the cave in the clefts of</l>
<l>the big mountain,</l>
<l rend="indent">where the broad-trunked elephant bull,</l>
<l rend="indent2">embraced by [his] youthful female with a calf,</l>
<l rend="indent">after he had ruined the big trunk [as] strong as a hillock,</l>
<l rend="indent2">since [his] strength was superior,</l>
<l rend="indent3">while many sounding pearls made noise<note place="foot">This seems to be a/the Tamil variety of the topos of an elephant’s pearls: they grow in its tusks, and here, obviously, they even rattle. T.V.G.’s parallels all come from much later texts.</note></l>
<l rend="indent3">in [his] red tusks reeking of flesh,</l>
<l rend="indent3">reddened when he beat the tiger,</l>
<l rend="indent">feeds out protectively gold-like morsels from the Vēṅkai-tree</l>
<l>from which he had driven away large swarms</l>
<l>of [those that] make honey,</l>
<l>– look, may you live, little woman:</l>
<l rend="indent2">the wilderness, adorned with many-flowered Kōṅkam trees,</l>
<l rend="indent4">as the long chain of moving lights</l>
<l rend="indent4">in the month to do duty when the six stars have spread,<note place="foot">T.V.G. supplies the cultural background information: in the month of Karttikeya, the women of all houses would make chains of lights throughout the village.</note></l>
<l rend="indent4">[in the house] of your father.</l>
        </lg>
      </div>
    </body>
